## Plain-English Summary

### ✅ You CAN

- Self-host NightPigeon on your own Discord server(s) that you personally own or directly manage
- Modify the source code for your own private use
- Fork the repository for private development and learning

### ❌ You CANNOT

- Run a public instance of NightPigeon that other people or server owners can invite to their servers
- Offer NightPigeon (or any fork of it) as a hosted or shared bot service to others — even for free
- Create your own public-facing NightPigeon bot under any name or branding
- Charge for access to a running instance of NightPigeon
- Remove or obscure the original copyright notice in any distribution

### ⚠️ You MUST

- Keep this license file in any fork or copy of the code
- Keep the copyright notice intact in any source files you distribute

