## Full Terms

Permission is granted, free of charge, to any individual to obtain a copy
of this software and associated documentation files (the "Software") for the
sole purpose of self-hosting on Discord servers that you personally own or
directly administer, subject to the following restrictions:

1. **No public instances.** You may not operate any instance of the Software
   that is accessible to Discord servers, users, or server owners outside of
   your own. This includes running a public bot that others can invite, sharing
   a bot token for others to use, or operating the Software in any form where
   third parties can interact with it without your direct involvement. Running
   a bot that other server owners can invite to their guilds — under any name,
   branding, or fork — requires written permission from the copyright holders.

2. **No hosting as a service.** You may not offer the Software, or any
   modified version of it, as a service — whether free or paid — to third
   parties. You may not create a "public NightPigeon" or derivative thereof
   for others to use.

3. **Attribution.** Any fork or redistribution of the source code must retain
   the original copyright notice and this license file in full.

THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR
IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY,
FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE AND NON-INFRINGEMENT. IN NO EVENT SHALL THE
AUTHORS OR COPYRIGHT HOLDERS BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES, OR OTHER
LIABILITY, WHETHER IN AN ACTION OF CONTRACT, TORT, OR OTHERWISE, ARISING FROM,
OUT OF, OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE SOFTWARE OR THE USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN THE
